The SVM is used to provide the pulses for the DC–AC inverter switches. Some interesting advantages of this scheme are: [10.1016@j.conengprac.2019.05.003]
(i)	The reduction of the number of switch commutation;
(ii)	The reduction of the harmonic content of the output voltage; 
(iii)	A greater modulation index, which results in a better DC bus voltage;
(iv)	The easiness of implementation in microprocessors
The SVM algorithm adopted in this paper was initially proposed by Kim and Sul (1996), which is based on Kanchan, Baiju, Mohapatra, Ouseph, and Gopakumar (2005) and Krishna, Amarnath, and Kamakshiah (2012), as it has advantages in terms of hardware implementation.
